$interpreted: Leah: See! Found it~
Tica: I hear some strange sounds nearby...
Leah: Maybe it's the voices in your head?
Tica: Huh?
Leah: She's a big girl, will one stem be enough? Might as well bring back a few more.
Tica: Wait for me!
Tica: Why is this plant so gigantic? And when did they start attacking humans...
Leah: I-I-I-I-I think we should run.
Tica: Sorry for taking so long!
Fatima: Hmph. I thought you both were gone for good.
Tica: While gathering your herbs, a bunch of scary plants attacked us,
Tica: so it took us longer than usual.
Fatima: You went deep into the forest, didn't you?
Tica: Yeah, what's the matter?
Fatima: Not long ago, my tribe witnessed a giant flower swallowing a strange looking seed.
Fatima: Ever since, not only did that giant flower become aggressive, the surrounding plants also became engulfed in fury and rage.
Tica: What? How did this happen?
Fatima: This event greatly endangered the lives of Panthers. That's why I've been on patrol.
Leah: The seed you mentioned...can you tell us more?
Fatima: I believe it was green, with protrusions and ridges.
Tica: Protrusion...? That's it! My sixth sense tells me...
Tica: ...that's the seed Headmaster Ceres wants!
Leah: Alright~ If we share the same goal, how about putting our differences aside, and working together to beat that plant?
Fatima: I accept. But after retrieving the seed, you must both leave Panther territory!
Tica: You've got it!
Leah: Weeheehee, fabulous~ One more dummy to protect me.
